ht|j|cs|6|AT|

^B{|ia|,1dp2dp?|at|} ^M After a 2x inverted raise, obligations are as follows:|
PG| ***** 111 ***** |


AT|

a) New suits by both opener and responder show stoppers. Skipping a suit denies a stopper in that suit (e.g. 1D-2D-2S denies a heart stopper). The auction is forcing to either at least 2N or 3 of the minor.|ht|j|AT|

^B{|ia|,1dp2dp2S|at|}|
PG| ***** 112 ***** |


ht|r|AT|

b) If responder has a game forcing hand (13 or more), it is his responsibility to make sure their side gets to game. New suits are forcing.|
PG| ***** 113 ***** |


